currentPositions.description:
Professional Field Service Engineer with expertise in various systems related to 
hospital automation. Assessment of mechanical, electronic and software systems for 
parts repair, replacement, and integration. Review and analyze performance issues 
and recommend corrective action where needed.

Role:
1.TraspoNet System Engineering. Configuration, Preventative Maintenance and 
Service for European Standard Pneumatic Tube System.
2.Translogic System Engineering. Configuration, Preventative Maintenance and 
Service for North American Standard Pneumatic Tube System.
3.PillPick Pharmacy Automation Unit-Dose Robot. Configuration, Preventative 
Maintenance and Service for Advanced Robotic Solution.
4.BoxPicker Pharmacy Automation High-Density Robot. Configuration, 
Preventative Maintenance, Service and Customer training for Advanced Robotic 
Solution.
5.Automated Dispensing Cabinet (ADC). Configuration, Preventative Maintenance 
Service and customer training for innovative ADC system and software solutions.
currentPositions.title: Customer Service Specialist

ingestedContentSummary.fullText: In order to keep a project on track from kickoff to completion, it's critical that you have a mastery of integration management. Project Integration Management ensures all processes in a project run smoothly, and results in a properly synchronized series of deliverables such as the project charter and plan. In this course, Oliver Yarbrough details how to properly approach Project Integration Management, providing project managers with tactical knowledge on how to successfully integrate all the components of a project. Along the way, Oliver goes over each of the key processes in the Project Integration Management Knowledge Area; shares best practices for managing project constraints and facilitating interactions; and acquaints you with emerging trends, including artificial intelligence.
